      "content": "Serotonin syndrome can be life-threatening, and even infrequent or low doses of St. John's wort can interact with sertraline. The risk isn't just theoretical; it's real and can occur even with minimal exposure. The body is complex, and even small changes can have significant effects. It's crucial to prioritize your health and seek professional advice before making any changes to your medication regimen. Remember, prevention is always better than dealing with the consequences of a potentially dangerous reaction.",
